abstract: A company with deep ties to Gov. Chris Christie dominates New Jersey’s system of large halfway houses. There has been little state oversight, despite widespread problems.
snippet: A company with deep ties to Gov. Chris Christie dominates New Jersey’s system of large halfway houses. There has been little state oversight, despite widespread problems.
lead_paragraph: After serving more than a year behind bars in New Jersey for assaulting a former girlfriend, David Goodell was transferred in 2010 to a sprawling halfway house in Newark. One night, Mr. Goodell escaped, but no one in authority paid much notice. He headed straight for the suburbs, for another young woman who had spurned him, and he killed her, the police said.

snippet: The Spanish operator is seeking to raise as much as 2.5 billion euros to help pay down debt.
lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Telefónica, the largest European telecom operator by sales, said Thursday that it planned to sell a stake in its German carrier, O2 Germany, and would weigh similar sales at some of its Latin American carriers as it looked to trim debt following a credit review.
